data.title: Printing and Publishing
data.text:
CG-612 Directives and Publications Division

Washington, DC

Printing and Publishing

CG-612 Printing Program Roles and Responsibilities: Serves as the U.S. Coast Guard liaison between USCG Headquarters, Government Publishing Office, other government agencies/joint services, and USCG customers. Coordinates the requirements regarding the production of organization publications, printed and processed materials, and directs the Government Publishing Office representatives and Government Publishing Office approved contractors in the production and budgetary requirements for printing.

United States Coast Guard Printing and Binding Regulations
